<Link id="l00024" /><CodeLine lineNumber="24"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Value in the MCInst. The immediate Value has had any PC adjustment made by</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00026" /><CodeLine lineNumber="26"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// else false. If the getOpInfo() function was set as part of the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00027" /><CodeLine lineNumber="27"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// setupForSymbolicDisassembly() call then that function is called to get any</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00028" /><CodeLine lineNumber="28"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// symbolic information at the Address for this instruction. If that returns</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00029" /><CodeLine lineNumber="29"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// non-zero then the symbolic information it returns is used to create an MCExpr</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00030" /><CodeLine lineNumber="30"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// and that is added as an operand to the MCInst. If getOpInfo() returns zero</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00031" /><CodeLine lineNumber="31"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// and IsBranch is true then a symbol look up for Value is done and if a symbol</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00032" /><CodeLine lineNumber="32"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// is found an MCExpr is created with that, else an MCExpr with Value is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00033" /><CodeLine lineNumber="33"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// created. This function returns true if it adds an operand to the MCInst and</span></CodeLine>
